steps.instruction:
1. Position a rack to the top third of your oven
2. Preheat your oven to 425F
3. In a large bowl, mix together the flour, cheese powder, baking powder, salt and pumpkin pie spice
4. Work in the cold butter just until the mixture is unevenly crumbly
5. Put in the grated cheddar, mix to combine
6. Add in the pumpkin, mix to combine
7. Stir the dough until it is evenly moistened and holds together adding milk a tablespoon at a time (you can add up to 2 tablespoons of milk)
8. Turn the dough out to a lightly floured surface
9. Flatten into a 3/4" thick disk 
10. Cut the biscuits with a 3" biscuit cutter
11. Lightly grease a baking sheet or line it with parchment paper
12. Space out the biscuits onto the pan
13. Brush the tops of the biscuits with milk or melted butter (this just makes them pretty)
14. Bake for 18 to 20 minutes
15 Serve warm
